If you're on a normal server, the top guild has been farming NToV for at least 4 or 5 months. That's enough time to get almost everybody decked out in NToV loot, and almost everybody in the guild a piece of Vulak loot.<br>
<br>
So, patch day comes around - and NToV is made harder. It's not the 4-5 hour breeze-through clearing anymore, and since most of the loot is either rotting, being sold off to people the zone, or going to twinks.. your guild decides it isn't worth the 8-9 hours to clear, especially with no Vulak at the end. End result? #1 guilds leave NToV alone, and the underdog guilds have free reign of it.<br>
<br>
